.. activecode:: conditional_execution_AC_1
   :author: bmiller
   :difficulty: 3.0
   :basecourse: thinkcpp
   :topic: Chapter4/ConditionalExecution
   :from_source: T
   :language: cpp
   :caption: Testing Values of x

   This program shows how you can use conditional statements to
   assess true/false situations.
   ~~~~
   #include <iostream>
   using namespace std;

   int main () {
       int x = 12;
       if (x == 12) {
           cout << "Equal!" << endl;
       }
       if (x != 13) {
           cout << "Not equal!" << endl;
       }
       if (x < 6) {
           cout << "Bigger!" << endl;
       }
       return 0;
   }

